# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values. Never commit `.env.local`.
# Vite docs: https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode.html
#
# Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to browser code via import.meta.env.
# Those values are still embedded in the built client bundle — use a server or serverless
# proxy for keys that must stay private (e.g. OpenAI).

# Example (uncomment and set when you add a client-safe public URL):
# VITE_PUBLIC_API_URL=

# Example placeholder for a future public analytics or feature flag ID (never commit real values here):
# VITE_PUBLIC_SOME_ID=
